OL,3,C'It is heartbreaking': Hospices under
OL,4,Cpressure as 70% face financial deficit
OL,6,FMy mum Diane was 51 when she was
OL,7,Fdiagnosed with breast cancer.
OL,9,FShe endured countless rounds of
OL,10,Fgruelling chemotherapy, and for five
OL,11,Fyears managed to live a largely full
OL,12,Fand active life alongside her
OL,13,Ftreatment, free of debilitating pain.
OL,15,FAt the beginning of 2014 her condition
OL,16,Fdeteriorated quickly. The final few
OL,17,Fdays of my mum's life were beyond
OL,18,Ftough. Her bravery knew no bounds, but
OL,19,Fbravery is not enough in the face of
OL,20,Fcancer.
