OL,3,C'It is heartbreaking': Hospices under
OL,4,Cpressure as 70% face financial deficit
OL,6,FThere are not enough words in the
OL,7,Fworld to describe the unending
OL,8,Fgratitude we have for the palliative
OL,9,Fcare nurse who came to our house from
OL,10,FSt Giles Hospice in Staffordshire, and
OL,11,Fmade my mum comfortable.
OL,13,FIt meant she could stay in her own
OL,14,Fhome, in her own bed, surrounded by
OL,15,Ffamily.
OL,17,FUntil that time, I had no idea what
OL,18,Fhospices really did. To me, I
OL,19,Fignorantly thought they were nice
OL,20,Fplaces where old people went to die.
