OL,3,C'It is heartbreaking': Hospices under
OL,4,Cpressure as 70% face financial deficit
OL,6,FI soon discovered that ignorance is
OL,7,Fwidely shared, as is the
OL,8,Funderstanding, or lack of, of how
OL,9,Fhospices are actually funded.
OL,11,FThe work of hospices is both precious
OL,12,Fand precarious. The vast majority of
OL,13,Fend-of-life care that they deliver is
OL,14,Fpaid for through donations.
OL,16,FMy mum died with dignity, at home,
OL,17,Fbecause someone somewhere held a
OL,18,Fcoffee morning, or donated some old
OL,19,Fclothes to their local charity shop,
OL,20,For ran a marathon.
