OL,3,C'It is heartbreaking': Hospices under
OL,4,Cpressure as 70% face financial deficit
OL,6,FThe government provides, on average,
OL,7,Fjust a third of hospice funding.
OL,8,FChildren's hospices receive even less.
OL,10,FIt costs around #1.6 billion a year to
OL,11,Frun the UK's 200 or so hospices. #1.1
OL,12,Fbillion of that is raised by the
OL,13,Fhospices themselves through
OL,14,Ffundraising.
OL,16,FThat is hard enough in good times, but
OL,17,Fin both economic and health terms,
OL,18,Fthese are not good times. To put it
OL,19,Fbluntly, slowly but surely hospices
OL,20,Fare running out of money.
