OL,6,F"It is heartbreaking and it's absolute
OL,7,Fmadness. If we have 23 beds, we can
OL,8,Frelieve more pressure from an already
OL,9,Fstruggling (NHS) system but we
OL,10,Fliterally can't afford to do it."
OL,12,FHospices are charitable organisations
OL,13,Fbut they play a crucial role in the
OL,14,Fhealthcare system, taking patients out
OL,15,Fof NHS hospitals and away from NHS
OL,16,Fservices.
OL,18,FNatalie Morris has already noticed a
OL,19,Fdifference in the care hospices are
OL,20,Fproviding.
