OL,6,F"It just caught us completely out of
OL,7,Fthe blue. She'd been unwell, and the
OL,8,Fdoctors weren't sure what it was.
OL,10,F"A part of my brain was like, surely
OL,11,Fnot, surely this can't happen again so
OL,12,Fsoon to our family? It's not our turn
OL,13,Fagain, surely?"
OL,15,FDiagnosed with pancreatic cancer, Kim
OL,16,Fknew that she was dying. After seeing
OL,17,Fwhat Tony had been through, she began
OL,18,Fto plan her own hospice care, albeit
OL,19,Fat a different one near where she
OL,20,Flived.
