OL,6,FNatalie said: "She was really
OL,7,Fproactive. She went to visit hospices,
OL,8,Fshe made a plan with her GP, and she
OL,9,Fwas very clear that was the path she
OL,10,Fwanted to go down.
OL,12,F"When it got to that point where she
OL,13,Fcould no longer be at home...she
OL,14,Fdidn't want to be at hospital. She
OL,15,Fwanted to be in a hospice."
OL,17,FDespite becoming seriously ill only
OL,18,Ffour years apart, the contrast in care
OL,19,FTony and Kim received could not have
OL,20,Fbeen more different.
