OL,6,FNatalie watched as the careful
OL,7,Frequests her mum had made for a
OL,8,Fdignified death failed to materialise.
OL,9,FShe says Kim's hospice stay was no
OL,10,Fdifferent to being in an over-run,
OL,11,Funder-resourced hospital.
OL,13,F"The staff were trying their hardest,
OL,14,Fit felt like the resources had been
OL,15,Fpretty brutally stripped," she said.
OL,17,F"For her to be in such a vulnerable
OL,18,Fstate, to be on a shared ward with
OL,19,Fother people, all we could do was pull
OL,20,Fa thin curtain around her bed.
