OL,3,C'It is heartbreaking': Hospices under
OL,4,Cpressure as 70% face financial deficit
OL,6,FOur experience with the hospice was
OL,7,Fshort. Some people rely on them for
OL,8,Fmany years, their conditions incurable
OL,9,Fbut manageable, and their lives are
OL,10,Flived better as a result.
OL,12,FHospices do so much - respite care,
OL,13,Fphysiotherapy, rehabilitation, pain
OL,14,Fand symptom control, physiological
OL,15,Fsupport, financial advice.
OL,17,FFor the vast majority of people who
OL,18,Fcome into contact with a hospice, they
OL,19,Fare not places where people go to die,
OL,20,Ffor many they are places where people
OL,21,Fto go live.
